$lastKnown) / max($lastKnown, 1) < 0.1) {\n                    return $approximate;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Fall back to exact count (but limit execution time)\n        try {\n            $sql = \"SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM `{$table}`\";\n            if (!empty($whereClause)) {\n                $sql .= \" WHERE {$whereClause}\";\n            }\n            \n            $startTime = microtime(true);\n            $result = $conn->query($sql);\n            $executionTime = microtime(true) -
